headline.main: THIRTY-THIRD CONGRESS......First Session.; SENATE, HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES.

docs.lead_paragraph: Mr. FESSENDEN presented a petition from New-Hampshire, praying for the repeal of the Fugitive Slave law. He said that the petition was not open to the objections of locality which had been urged against the memorial of the men of Boston.

headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; NEW-YORK UNIVERSITY. Anniversary of the Alumni. ] Trail for a Divorce. SUPERIOR COURT COURT CALENDAR

docs.lead_paragraph: The Annual Celebration of the Association of the Alumni of the New-York University took place on Tuesday evening. The proceedings were opened with prayer by Rev. Dr. FERRIS, Chancellor of the University, after which Prof. BENJAMIN N. MARTIN, the orator on the occasion, addressed the members of the Alumni, and a numerous and select audience.

docs.lead_paragraph: If meat were furnished as cheap as water, it would be esteemed too severe a tusk to eat it during such hot weather. But when it costs so enormously, and has no special merit of wholesomeness to commend it, we certainly should be excused from its use.

headline.main: HAVANA.; Celebration of Corpus Christi-Bunker Hill Anniversary at Havana--The Spanish Consul at N. Orleans-Importation of Negros, &c. News--Rumors and Miscellaneous Items.

docs.lead_paragraph: On the 15th, the celebration of "Corpus Christi" by procession, high mass , was the most brilliant that I have witnessed in Havana, for the last thirty years; and we had the pleasure of seeing the Viceroy and the Lord Bishop of the diocese in attendance, following the consecrated "bread and wind," which had become the veritable "body and blood" of the Saviour of the World.

headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; NEW-YORK UNIVERSITY. Annual Commencement at Niblo's.

docs.lead_paragraph: The usual exercises of the Annual Commencement of the New- York University took place yesterday, at Niblo's Garden. The first and second circles and parquette were densely crowded, while no inconsiderable number were compelled to take seats in the third circle.
